==English==

===Etymology===
Conjunction of {{m|en|safe|gloss=not in danger}} and {{m|en|sound|gloss=healthy}}. Compare with {{cog|fro|sauf et sain}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Having come to no [[harm]], especially after being exposed to [[danger]].
#: {{syn|en|in one piece|unharmed|unhurt|uninjured|unscathed}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Comedy of Errors|act=IV|scene=iv|page=96|passage=Come to the Centaur, fetch our ſtuffe from thence: / I long that we were '''ſafe and ſound''' aboord.}}

